gen

Class GoldTransitions

  • java.lang.Object
    • gen.GoldTransitions

  • public class GoldTransitions
extends Object
    A static class that contains functions to get the gold transitions to be applied to a vertex.

    • Method Detail

      • getGoldActionFirstStage

        public static String getGoldActionFirstStage(Amr amr,
                                             Vertex vertex)
        This function returns the gold transition for the first stage, i.e. one of MERGE, SWAP, DELETE and KEEP. Although DELETE-REENTRANCE transitions are also part of the first stage, they are handled deterministically via DirectedGraph.convertToTree() during the preprocessing performed by Amr.prepare(List, MaxentTagger, boolean).
        Parameters:
        amr - the AMR graph to which the vertex belongs
        vertex - the vertex
        Returns:
        the gold transition, which is one of MERGE, SWAP, KEEP and DELETE

      • getGoldMerge

        public static String getGoldMerge(Amr amr,
                                  Vertex vertex)
        This function returns either the gold merge transition to be applied to a vertex, or null if no merge transition is required.
        Parameters:
        amr - the AMR graph to which the vertex belongs
        vertex - the vertex
        Returns:
        a tab-separated string containing the concept and POS of the gold merge, if a MERGE transition is required, and null otherwise

      • getGoldSwap

        public static boolean getGoldSwap(Amr amr,
                                  Vertex vertex)
        This function returns whether a SWAP transition needs to be applied to some vertex.
        Parameters:
        amr - the AMR graph to which the vertex belongs
        vertex - the vertex
        Returns:
        true iff a SWAP transition needs to be applied

      • getGoldRealization

        public static String getGoldRealization(Amr amr,
                                        Edge edge)
        This function returns the gold REALIZE transition to be applied to some vertex.
        Parameters:
        amr - the AMR graph to which the vertex belongs
        edge - the instance edge of the vertex
        Returns:
        the realization of the vertex or an empty string if no realization is found

      • getGoldChildInsertion

        public static List<String> getGoldChildInsertion(Amr amr,
                                                 Vertex vertex)
        This function returns the gold INSERT_CHILD transition to be applied to some vertex.
        Parameters:
        amr - the AMR graph to which the vertex belongs
        vertex - the vertex
        Returns:
        the list of all words which have to be inserted through INSERT_CHILD transitions

      • getGoldBetweenInsertion

        public static List<String> getGoldBetweenInsertion(Amr amr,
                                                   Edge edge)
        This function returns the gold INSERT_BETWEEN transition to be applied to some vertex.
        Parameters:
        amr - the AMR graph to which the vertex belongs
        edge - the edge such that INSERT_BETWEEN is applied when edge.from is the top element of the node buffer and edge.to is the top element of the child buffer
        Returns:
        the word which has to be inserted through INSERT_BETWEEN transitions or an empty string if no such word exists. As we consider both the dependency-tree based and agnostic approaches, they both may give different results so a list containing both results is returned.

      • getGoldParentChildOrder

        public static String getGoldParentChildOrder(Amr amr,
                                             Edge parentInstanceEdge,
                                             Edge e)
        This function returns the gold order for two vertices, one of which is a child of the other. This is the equivalent of the <* relation introduced in Section 4.2.1 Modeling.
        Parameters:
        amr - the AMR graph to which both vertices belong
        parentInstanceEdge - the instance edge of the parent vertex
        e - the edge connecting the parent and child node
        Returns:
        the gold order for both vertices, or an empty string, if no meaningful order can be derived

      • getGoldSiblingOrder

        public static String getGoldSiblingOrder(Amr amr,
                                         Edge e1,
                                         Edge e2)
        This function returns the gold order for two vertices which are siblings. This is the equivalent of the <l and <r relations introduced in Section 4.2.1 Modeling.
        Parameters:
        amr - the AMR graph to which both vertices belong
        e1 - the edge connecting the common parent of both edges to the first child
        e2 - the edge connecting the common parent of both edges to the second child
        Returns:
        the gold order for both vertices, or an empty string, if no meaningful order can be derived
